The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Nov. 20: The RBI has relaxed the norms for foreign direct investment (FDI) in credit information companies by allowing reputed overseas firms to pick up a 49 per cent stake in Indian outfits. The Reserve Bank will now consider allowing 49 per cent FDI in companies with an established credit information bureau in a well regulated environment, the apex bank said.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 20: The countrys inflation rate fell to 8.9 per cent, a five-and-half-month low on the back of lower commodity and oil prices. This could prompt the Reserve Bank of India to lower interest rates.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 20: India will consider raising the ceiling on foreign institutional investment (FII) in the bond market once the current limit is exhausted, finance minister P. Chidambaram said. Theres enough headroom, he said.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 20: ONGC Videsh Ltd (OVL), the overseas arm of state-run Oil and Natural Gas Corporation, will make an open offer to acquire shares of Imperial Energy at 12.50 a share by December 9. The Russian government has approved of OVL taking over Imperial.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 20: Assocham has asked the government to reduce corporate and service taxes to boost demand. There should be a review of taxes, because this tax regime was during the boom time. We need special one-time tax concessions, Assocham president Sajjan Jindal said.                                                                                                                         
